arch:property.oc:show_val: Soil abutting Locus 18 Stairs of the Residential Quarter
2.00 m north south-by-1.27 m east west.
West Precinct Wall and the Residential Quarter Steps.
Closing elevation: 902.154 m, 2.00 m below Sub Datum P.

This sun-baked dusty fine soil is a Munsell Reddish Yellow 7.5YR 5/6 which has accumulated over the years. As this was a cleaning operation to expose the architecture of the West Precinct Wall and the Residential Quarter Steps, material culture was prolific.
Opening elevation: Locus 18 Stairs or the West Precinct Wall, approximately at Sub Datum P or 904.154 m.
Phase XIII: Major collapses continue into the Islamic period.
